# ============================================================================
# Meta-Flow Docker Environment Configuration
# ============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env and add your API keys:
#   cp .env.docker.example .env
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# LLM Provider API Keys (at least ONE required)
# ============================================================================

# Option 1: Anthropic Claude (Recommended for best performance)
# Get your API key from: https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5

# Option 2: AIMLAPI (OpenAI-compatible, supports multiple models)
# Get your API key from: https://aimlapi.com/
AIMLAPI_KEY=
AIMLAPI_MODEL=x-ai/grok-4-fast-reasoning

# Option 3: Google Gemini (Good alternative)
# Get your API key from: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-pro

# ============================================================================
# Quick Start Guide
# ============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.docker.example .env
#
# 2. Add at least ONE API key above (remove the empty value, add your key)
#
# 3. Build and start services:
#    ./start.sh
#    OR
#    docker-compose up --build
#
# 4. Access the application:
#    - Frontend: http://localhost
#    - Backend API: http://localhost:8000
#    - API Docs: http://localhost:8000/docs
#
# 5. To stop services:
#    ./stop.sh
#    OR
#    docker-compose down

# ============================================================================
# Notes
# ============================================================================
# - At least ONE of the above API keys is required for the system to work
# - The system will automatically detect which provider is configured
# - You can configure multiple providers for fallback/testing
# - Default models are shown above and can be customized
# - Models are validated at startup; invalid models will cause errors

# ============================================================================
# Troubleshooting
# ============================================================================
# If backend fails to start:
#   - Check that at least one API key is configured
#   - Verify the API key is valid (starts with correct prefix)
#   - Check logs: docker-compose logs backend
#
# If frontend can't connect to backend:
#   - Ensure backend is healthy: docker-compose ps
#   - Test backend directly: curl http://localhost:8000/api/health
#   - Check nginx logs: docker-compose logs frontend